220 unsigned StlrOp, unsigned CmpOp, unsigned ExtendImm, unsigned ZeroReg, ----
221 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
222 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
223 MIMetadata MIMD(MI); 0
224 const MachineOperand &Dest = MI.getOperand(0); 0
225 Register StatusReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
226 bool StatusDead = MI.getOperand(1).isDead(); 0
227 // Duplicating undef operands into 2 instructions does not guarantee the same ----
228 // value on both; However undef should be replaced by xzr anyway. ----
229 assert(!MI.getOperand(2).isUndef() && "cannot handle undef"); 0

236 auto StoreBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0

239 MF->insert(++MBB.getIterator(), LoadCmpBB); 0
240 MF->insert(++LoadCmpBB->getIterator(), StoreBB); 0
241 MF->insert(++StoreBB->getIterator(), DoneBB); 0

243 // .Lloadcmp: ----
244 // mov wStatus, 0 ----

246 // cmp xDest, xDesired ----
247 // b.ne .Ldone ----
248 if (!StatusDead) 0

261 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
262 LoadCmpBB->addSuccessor(StoreBB); 0
263 ----
264 // .Lstore: ----
265 // stlxr wStatus, xNew, [xAddr] ----
266 // cbnz wStatus, .Lloadcmp ----
267 BuildMI(StoreBB, MIMD, TII->get(StlrOp), StatusReg) 0
268 .addReg(NewReg) 0
269 .addReg(AddrReg); 0
270 BuildMI(StoreBB, MIMD, TII->get(AArch64::CBNZW)) 0
271 .addReg(StatusReg, getKillRegState(StatusDead)) 0
272 .addMBB(LoadCmpBB); 0
273 StoreBB->addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
274 StoreBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
275 ----
276 DoneBB->splice(DoneBB->end(), &MBB, MI, MBB.end()); 0
277 DoneBB->transferSuccessors(&MBB); 0
278 ----
279 MBB.addSuccessor(LoadCmpBB); 0
280 ----
281 NextMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
282 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
283 ----
284 // Recompute livein lists. ----
285 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs; 0
286 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *DoneBB); 0
287 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
288 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
289 // Do an extra pass around the loop to get loop carried registers right. ----
290 StoreBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
291 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *StoreBB); 0
292 LoadCmpBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
293 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoadCmpBB); 0
294 ----
295 return true; 0
296 } 0

434 /// \brief Expand Pseudos to Instructions with destructive operands. ----
435 /// ----
436 /// This mechanism uses MOVPRFX instructions for zeroing the false lanes ----
437 /// or for fixing relaxed register allocation conditions to comply with ----
438 /// the instructions register constraints. The latter case may be cheaper ----
439 /// than setting the register constraints in the register allocator, ----
440 /// since that will insert regular MOV instructions rather than MOVPRFX. ----
441 /// ----
442 /// Example (after register allocation): ----
443 /// ----
444 /// FSUB_ZPZZ_ZERO_B Z0, Pg, Z1, Z0 ----
445 /// ----
446 /// * The Pseudo FSUB_ZPZZ_ZERO_B maps to FSUB_ZPmZ_B. ----
447 /// * We cannot map directly to FSUB_ZPmZ_B because the register ----
448 /// constraints of the instruction are not met. ----
449 /// * Also the _ZERO specifies the false lanes need to be zeroed. ----
450 /// ----
451 /// We first try to see if the destructive operand == result operand, ----
452 /// if not, we try to swap the operands, e.g. ----
453 /// ----
454 /// FSUB_ZPmZ_B Z0, Pg/m, Z0, Z1 ----
455 /// ----
456 /// But because FSUB_ZPmZ is not commutative, this is semantically ----
457 /// different, so we need a reverse instruction: ----
458 /// ----
459 /// FSUBR_ZPmZ_B Z0, Pg/m, Z0, Z1 ----
460 /// ----
461 /// Then we implement the zeroing of the false lanes of Z0 by adding ----
462 /// a zeroing MOVPRFX instruction: ----
463 /// ----
464 /// MOVPRFX_ZPzZ_B Z0, Pg/z, Z0 ----
465 /// FSUBR_ZPmZ_B Z0, Pg/m, Z0, Z1 ----
466 /// ----
467 /// Note that this can only be done for _ZERO or _UNDEF variants where ----
468 /// we can guarantee the false lanes to be zeroed (by implementing this) ----
469 /// or that they are undef (don't care / not used), otherwise the ----
470 /// swapping of operands is illegal because the operation is not ----
471 /// (or cannot be emulated to be) fully commutative. ----
472 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expand_DestructiveOp( 0
473 MachineInstr &MI, ----
474 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
475 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
476 unsigned Opcode = AArch64::getSVEPseudoMap(MI.getOpcode()); 0
477 uint64_t DType = TII->get(Opcode).TSFlags & AArch64::DestructiveInstTypeMask; 0
478 uint64_t FalseLanes = MI.getDesc().TSFlags & AArch64::FalseLanesMask; 0
479 bool FalseZero = FalseLanes == AArch64::FalseLanesZero; 0
480 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
481 bool DstIsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead(); 0
482 bool UseRev = false; 0
483 unsigned PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx, Src2Idx; ----
484 ----
485 switch (DType) { 0
486 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryComm: 0
487 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryCommWithRev: ----
488 if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(3).getReg()) { 0
489 // FSUB Zd, Pg, Zs1, Zd ==> FSUBR Zd, Pg/m, Zd, Zs1 ----
490 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx) = std::make_tuple(1, 3, 2); 0
491 UseRev = true; 0
492 break; 0
493 } ----
494 [[fallthrough]]; ----
495 case AArch64::DestructiveBinary: ----
496 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryImm: ----
497 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx) = std::make_tuple(1, 2, 3); 0
498 break; 0
499 case AArch64::DestructiveUnaryPassthru: 0
500 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx) = std::make_tuple(2, 3, 3); 0
501 break; 0
502 case AArch64::DestructiveTernaryCommWithRev: 0
503 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx, Src2Idx) = std::make_tuple(1, 2, 3, 4); 0
504 if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(3).getReg()) { 0
505 // FMLA Zd, Pg, Za, Zd, Zm ==> FMAD Zdn, Pg, Zm, Za ----
506 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx, Src2Idx) = std::make_tuple(1, 3, 4, 2); 0
507 UseRev = true; 0
508 } else if (DstReg == MI.getOperand(4).getReg()) { 0
509 // FMLA Zd, Pg, Za, Zm, Zd ==> FMAD Zdn, Pg, Zm, Za ----
510 std::tie(PredIdx, DOPIdx, SrcIdx, Src2Idx) = std::make_tuple(1, 4, 3, 2); 0
511 UseRev = true; 0
512 } ----
513 break; 0
514 default: 0
515 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported Destructive Operand type"); 0
516 } ----
517 ----
518 // MOVPRFX can only be used if the destination operand ----
519 // is the destructive operand, not as any other operand, ----
520 // so the Destructive Operand must be unique. ----
521 bool DOPRegIsUnique = false; 0
522 switch (DType) { 0
523 case AArch64::DestructiveBinary: 0
524 DOPRegIsUnique = DstReg != MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg(); 0
525 break; 0
526 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryComm: 0
527 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryCommWithRev: ----
528 DOPRegIsUnique = 0
529 DstReg != MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg() || 0
530 MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg() != MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg(); 0
531 break; 0
532 case AArch64::DestructiveUnaryPassthru: 0
533 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryImm: ----
534 DOPRegIsUnique = true; 0
535 break; 0
536 case AArch64::DestructiveTernaryCommWithRev: 0
537 DOPRegIsUnique = 0
538 DstReg != MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg() || 0
539 (MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg() != MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg() && 0
540 MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg() != MI.getOperand(Src2Idx).getReg()); 0
541 break; 0
542 } ----
543 ----
544 // Resolve the reverse opcode ----
545 if (UseRev) { 0
546 int NewOpcode; ----
547 // e.g. DIV -> DIVR ----
548 if ((NewOpcode = AArch64::getSVERevInstr(Opcode)) != -1) 0
549 Opcode = NewOpcode; 0
550 // e.g. DIVR -> DIV ----
551 else if ((NewOpcode = AArch64::getSVENonRevInstr(Opcode)) != -1) 0
552 Opcode = NewOpcode; 0
553 } ----
554 ----
555 // Get the right MOVPRFX ----
556 uint64_t ElementSize = TII->getElementSizeForOpcode(Opcode); 0
557 unsigned MovPrfx, LSLZero, MovPrfxZero; ----
558 switch (ElementSize) { 0
559 case AArch64::ElementSizeNone: 0
560 case AArch64::ElementSizeB: ----
561 MovPrfx = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZZ; 0
562 LSLZero = AArch64::LSL_ZPmI_B; 0
563 MovPrfxZero = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZPzZ_B; 0
564 break; 0
565 case AArch64::ElementSizeH: 0
566 MovPrfx = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZZ; 0
567 LSLZero = AArch64::LSL_ZPmI_H; 0
568 MovPrfxZero = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZPzZ_H; 0
569 break; 0
570 case AArch64::ElementSizeS: 0
571 MovPrfx = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZZ; 0
572 LSLZero = AArch64::LSL_ZPmI_S; 0
573 MovPrfxZero = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZPzZ_S; 0
574 break; 0
575 case AArch64::ElementSizeD: 0
576 MovPrfx = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZZ; 0
577 LSLZero = AArch64::LSL_ZPmI_D; 0
578 MovPrfxZero = AArch64::MOVPRFX_ZPzZ_D; 0
579 break; 0
580 default: 0
581 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ElementSize"); 0
582 } ----
583 ----
584 // ----
585 // Create the destructive operation (if required) ----
586 // ----
587 MachineInstrBuilder PRFX, DOP; 0
588 if (FalseZero) { 0
589 // If we cannot prefix the requested instruction we'll instead emit a ----
590 // prefixed_zeroing_mov for DestructiveBinary. ----
591 assert((DOPRegIsUnique || DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinary || 0
592 DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinaryComm || ----
593 DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinaryCommWithRev) && ----
594 "The destructive operand should be unique"); ----
595 assert(ElementSize != AArch64::ElementSizeNone && 0
596 "This instruction is unpredicated"); ----
597 ----
598 // Merge source operand into destination register ----
599 PRFX = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(MovPrfxZero)) 0
600 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
601 .addReg(MI.getOperand(PredIdx).getReg()) 0
602 .addReg(MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg()); 0
603 ----
604 // After the movprfx, the destructive operand is same as Dst ----
605 DOPIdx = 0; 0
606 ----
607 // Create the additional LSL to zero the lanes when the DstReg is not ----
608 // unique. Zeros the lanes in z0 that aren't active in p0 with sequence ----
609 // movprfx z0.b, p0/z, z0.b; lsl z0.b, p0/m, z0.b, #0; ----
610 if ((DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinary || 0
611 DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinaryComm || 0
612 DType == AArch64::DestructiveBinaryCommWithRev) && 0
613 !DOPRegIsUnique) { 0
614 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(LSLZero)) 0
615 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
616 .add(MI.getOperand(PredIdx)) 0
617 .addReg(DstReg) 0
618 .addImm(0); 0
619 } ----
620 } else if (DstReg != MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg()) { 0
621 assert(DOPRegIsUnique && "The destructive operand should be unique"); 0
622 PRFX = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(MovPrfx)) 0
623 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define) 0
624 .addReg(MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg()); 0
625 DOPIdx = 0; 0
626 } ----
627 ----
628 // ----
629 // Create the destructive operation ----
630 // ----
631 DOP = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opcode)) 0
632 .addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(DstIsDead)); 0
633 ----
634 switch (DType) { 0
635 case AArch64::DestructiveUnaryPassthru: 0
636 DOP.addReg(MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg(), RegState::Kill) 0
637 .add(MI.getOperand(PredIdx)) 0
638 .add(MI.getOperand(SrcIdx)); 0
639 break; 0
640 case AArch64::DestructiveBinary: 0
641 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryImm: ----
642 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryComm: ----
643 case AArch64::DestructiveBinaryCommWithRev: ----
644 DOP.add(MI.getOperand(PredIdx)) 0
645 .addReg(MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg(), RegState::Kill) 0
646 .add(MI.getOperand(SrcIdx)); 0
647 break; 0
648 case AArch64::DestructiveTernaryCommWithRev: 0
649 DOP.add(MI.getOperand(PredIdx)) 0
650 .addReg(MI.getOperand(DOPIdx).getReg(), RegState::Kill) 0
651 .add(MI.getOperand(SrcIdx)) 0
652 .add(MI.getOperand(Src2Idx)); 0
653 break; 0
654 } ----
655 ----
656 if (PRFX) { 0
657 finalizeBundle(MBB, PRFX->getIterator(), MBBI->getIterator()); 0
658 transferImpOps(MI, PRFX, DOP); 0
659 } else ----
660 transferImpOps(MI, DOP, DOP); 0
661 ----
662 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
663 return true; 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandSetTagLoop( 0
667 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
668 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
669 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
670 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
671 Register SizeReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
672 Register AddressReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
673 ----
674 MachineFunction *MF = MBB.getParent(); 0
675 ----
676 bool ZeroData = MI.getOpcode() == AArch64::STZGloop_wback; 0
677 const unsigned OpCode1 = 0
678 ZeroData ? AArch64::STZGPostIndex : AArch64::STGPostIndex; 0
679 const unsigned OpCode2 = 0
680 ZeroData ? AArch64::STZ2GPostIndex : AArch64::ST2GPostIndex; 0
681 ----
682 unsigned Size = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
683 assert(Size > 0 && Size % 16 == 0); 0
684 if (Size % (16 * 2) != 0) { 0
685 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(OpCode1), AddressReg) 0
686 .addReg(AddressReg) 0
687 .addReg(AddressReg) 0
688 .addImm(1); 0
689 Size -= 16; 0
690 } ----
691 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = ----
692 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::MOVi64imm), SizeReg) 0
693 .addImm(Size); 0
694 expandMOVImm(MBB, I, 64); 0
695 ----
696 auto LoopBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
697 auto DoneBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB.getBasicBlock()); 0
698 ----
699 MF->insert(++MBB.getIterator(), LoopBB); 0
700 MF->insert(++LoopBB->getIterator(), DoneBB); 0
701 ----
702 BuildMI(LoopBB, DL, TII->get(OpCode2)) 0
703 .addDef(AddressReg) 0
704 .addReg(AddressReg) 0
705 .addReg(AddressReg) 0
706 .addImm(2) 0
707 .cloneMemRefs(MI) 0
708 .setMIFlags(MI.getFlags()); 0
709 BuildMI(LoopBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::SUBSXri)) 0
710 .addDef(SizeReg) 0
711 .addReg(SizeReg) 0
712 .addImm(16 * 2) 0
713 .addImm(0); 0
714 BuildMI(LoopBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::Bcc)) 0
715 .addImm(AArch64CC::NE) 0
716 .addMBB(LoopBB) 0
717 .addReg(AArch64::NZCV, RegState::Implicit | RegState::Kill); 0
718 ----
719 LoopBB->addSuccessor(LoopBB); 0
720 LoopBB->addSuccessor(DoneBB); 0
721 ----
722 DoneBB->splice(DoneBB->end(), &MBB, MI, MBB.end()); 0
723 DoneBB->transferSuccessors(&MBB); 0
724 ----
725 MBB.addSuccessor(LoopBB); 0
726 ----
727 NextMBBI = MBB.end(); 0
728 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
729 // Recompute liveness bottom up. ----
730 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs; 0
731 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *DoneBB); 0
732 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoopBB); 0
733 // Do an extra pass in the loop to get the loop carried dependencies right. ----
734 // FIXME: is this necessary? ----
735 LoopBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
736 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *LoopBB); 0
737 DoneBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
738 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *DoneBB); 0
739 ----
740 return true; 0
741 } 0
742 ----
743 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandSVESpillFill(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
744 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
745 unsigned Opc, unsigned N) { ----
746 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = ----
747 MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
748 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
749 for (unsigned Offset = 0; Offset < N; ++Offset) { 0
750 int ImmOffset = MI.getOperand(2).getImm() + Offset; 0
751 bool Kill = (Offset + 1 == N) ? MI.getOperand(1).isKill() : false; 0
752 assert(ImmOffset >= -256 && ImmOffset < 256 && 0
753 "Immediate spill offset out of range"); ----
754 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)) 0
755 .addReg( 0
756 TRI->getSubReg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), AArch64::zsub0 + Offset), 0
757 Opc == AArch64::LDR_ZXI ? RegState::Define : 0) ----
758 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), getKillRegState(Kill)) 0
759 .addImm(ImmOffset); 0
760 } ----
761 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
762 return true; 0
763 } ----
764 ----
765 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandCALL_RVMARKER( 0
766 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
767 // Expand CALL_RVMARKER pseudo to: ----
768 // - a branch to the call target, followed by ----
769 // - the special `mov x29, x29` marker, and ----
770 // - another branch, to the runtime function ----
771 // Mark the sequence as bundle, to avoid passes moving other code in between. ----
772 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
773 ----
774 MachineInstr *OriginalCall; ----
775 MachineOperand &RVTarget = MI.getOperand(0); 0
776 MachineOperand &CallTarget = MI.getOperand(1); 0
777 assert((CallTarget.isGlobal() || CallTarget.isReg()) && 0
778 "invalid operand for regular call"); ----
779 assert(RVTarget.isGlobal() && "invalid operand for attached call"); 0
780 unsigned Opc = CallTarget.isGlobal() ? AArch64::BL : AArch64::BLR; 0
781 OriginalCall = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)).getInstr(); 0
782 OriginalCall->addOperand(CallTarget); 0
783 ----
784 unsigned RegMaskStartIdx = 2; 0
785 // Skip register arguments. Those are added during ISel, but are not ----
786 // needed for the concrete branch. ----
787 while (!MI.getOperand(RegMaskStartIdx).isRegMask()) { 0
788 auto MOP = MI.getOperand(RegMaskStartIdx); 0
789 assert(MOP.isReg() && "can only add register operands"); 0
790 OriginalCall->addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg( 0
791 MOP.getReg(), /*Def=*/false, /*Implicit=*/true)); ----
792 RegMaskStartIdx++; 0
793 } ----
794 for (const MachineOperand &MO : 0
795 llvm::drop_begin(MI.operands(), RegMaskStartIdx)) 0
796 OriginalCall->addOperand(MO); 0
797 ----
798 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(AArch64::ORRXrs)) 0
799 .addReg(AArch64::FP, RegState::Define) 0
800 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
801 .addReg(AArch64::FP) 0
802 .addImm(0); 0
803 ----
804 auto *RVCall = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(AArch64::BL)) 0
805 .add(RVTarget) 0
806 .getInstr(); 0
807 ----
808 if (MI.shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
809 MBB.getParent()->moveCallSiteInfo(&MI, OriginalCall); 0
810 ----
811 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
812 finalizeBundle(MBB, OriginalCall->getIterator(), 0
813 std::next(RVCall->getIterator())); ----
814 return true; 0
815 } ----
816 ----
817 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandCALL_BTI(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
818 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
819 // Expand CALL_BTI pseudo to: ----
820 // - a branch to the call target ----
821 // - a BTI instruction ----
822 // Mark the sequence as a bundle, to avoid passes moving other code in ----
823 // between. ----
824 ----
825 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
826 MachineOperand &CallTarget = MI.getOperand(0); 0
827 assert((CallTarget.isGlobal() || CallTarget.isReg()) && 0
828 "invalid operand for regular call"); ----
829 unsigned Opc = CallTarget.isGlobal() ? AArch64::BL : AArch64::BLR; 0
830 MachineInstr *Call = ----
831 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)).getInstr(); 0
832 Call->addOperand(CallTarget); 0
833 Call->setCFIType(*MBB.getParent(), MI.getCFIType()); 0
834 ----
835 MachineInstr *BTI = ----
836 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(AArch64::HINT)) 0
837 // BTI J so that setjmp can to BR to this. ----
838 .addImm(36) 0
839 .getInstr(); 0
840 ----
841 if (MI.shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
842 MBB.getParent()->moveCallSiteInfo(&MI, Call); 0
843 ----
844 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
845 finalizeBundle(MBB, Call->getIterator(), std::next(BTI->getIterator())); 0
846 return true; 0
847 } ----
848 ----
849 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandStoreSwiftAsyncContext( 0
850 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
851 Register CtxReg = MBBI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
852 Register BaseReg = MBBI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
853 int Offset = MBBI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
854 DebugLoc DL(MBBI->getDebugLoc()); 0
855 auto &STI = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget(); 0
856 ----
857 if (STI.getTargetTriple().getArchName() != "arm64e") { 0
858 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::STRXui)) 0
859 .addUse(CtxReg) 0
860 .addUse(BaseReg) 0
861 .addImm(Offset / 8) 0
862 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
863 MBBI->eraseFromParent(); 0
864 return true; 0
865 } ----
866 ----
867 // We need to sign the context in an address-discriminated way. 0xc31a is a ----
868 // fixed random value, chosen as part of the ABI. ----
869 // add x16, xBase, #Offset ----
870 // movk x16, #0xc31a, lsl #48 ----
871 // mov x17, x22/xzr ----
872 // pacdb x17, x16 ----
873 // str x17, [xBase, #Offset] ----
874 unsigned Opc = Offset >= 0 ? AArch64::ADDXri : AArch64::SUBXri; 0
875 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(Opc), AArch64::X16) 0
876 .addUse(BaseReg) 0
877 .addImm(abs(Offset)) 0
878 .addImm(0) 0
879 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
880 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::MOVKXi), AArch64::X16) 0
881 .addUse(AArch64::X16) 0
882 .addImm(0xc31a) 0
883 .addImm(48) 0
884 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
885 // We're not allowed to clobber X22 (and couldn't clobber XZR if we tried), so ----
886 // move it somewhere before signing. ----
887 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::ORRXrs), AArch64::X17) 0
888 .addUse(AArch64::XZR) 0
889 .addUse(CtxReg) 0
890 .addImm(0) 0
891 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
892 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::PACDB), AArch64::X17) 0
893 .addUse(AArch64::X17) 0
894 .addUse(AArch64::X16) 0
895 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
896 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::STRXui)) 0
897 .addUse(AArch64::X17) 0
898 .addUse(BaseReg) 0
899 .addImm(Offset / 8) 0
900 .setMIFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup); 0
901 ----
902 MBBI->eraseFromParent(); 0
903 return true; 0
904 } 0
905 ----
906 MachineBasicBlock * ----
907 AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandRestoreZA(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
908 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
909 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
910 assert((std::next(MBBI) != MBB.end() || 0
911 MI.getParent()->successors().begin() != ----
912 MI.getParent()->successors().end()) && ----
913 "Unexpected unreachable in block that restores ZA"); ----
914 ----
915 // Compare TPIDR2_EL0 value against 0. ----
916 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
917 MachineInstrBuilder Cbz = BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AArch64::CBZX)) 0
918 .add(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
919 ----
920 // Split MBB and create two new blocks: ----
921 // - MBB now contains all instructions before RestoreZAPseudo. ----
922 // - SMBB contains the RestoreZAPseudo instruction only. ----
923 // - EndBB contains all instructions after RestoreZAPseudo. ----
924 MachineInstr &PrevMI = *std::prev(MBBI); 0
925 MachineBasicBlock *SMBB = MBB.splitAt(PrevMI, /*UpdateLiveIns*/ true); 0
926 MachineBasicBlock *EndBB = std::next(MI.getIterator()) == SMBB->end() 0
927 ? *SMBB->successors().begin() 0
928 : SMBB->splitAt(MI, /*UpdateLiveIns*/ true); 0
929 ----
930 // Add the SMBB label to the TB[N]Z instruction & create a branch to EndBB. ----
931 Cbz.addMBB(SMBB); 0
932 BuildMI(&MBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::B)) 0
933 .addMBB(EndBB); 0
934 MBB.addSuccessor(EndBB); 0
935 ----
936 // Replace the pseudo with a call (BL). ----
937 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
938 BuildMI(*SMBB, SMBB->end(), DL, TII->get(AArch64::BL)); 0
939 MIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), RegState::Implicit); 0
940 for (unsigned I = 2; I < MI.getNumOperands(); ++I) 0
941 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(I)); 0
942 BuildMI(SMBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::B)).addMBB(EndBB); 0
943 ----
944 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
945 return EndBB; 0
946 } 0
947 ----
948 MachineBasicBlock * ----
949 AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandCondSMToggle(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
950 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI) { ----
951 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
952 // In the case of a smstart/smstop before a unreachable, just remove the pseudo. ----
953 // Exception handling code generated by Clang may introduce unreachables and it ----
954 // seems unnecessary to restore pstate.sm when that happens. Note that it is ----
955 // not just an optimisation, the code below expects a successor instruction/block ----
956 // in order to split the block at MBBI. ----
957 if (std::next(MBBI) == MBB.end() && 0
958 MI.getParent()->successors().begin() == 0
959 MI.getParent()->successors().end()) { 0
960 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
961 return &MBB; 0
962 } ----
963 ----
964 // Expand the pseudo into smstart or smstop instruction. The pseudo has the ----
965 // following operands: ----
966 // ----
967 // MSRpstatePseudo , <0|1>, pstate.sm, expectedval, ----
968 // ----
969 // The pseudo is expanded into a conditional smstart/smstop, with a ----
970 // check if pstate.sm (register) equals the expected value, and if not, ----
971 // invokes the smstart/smstop. ----
972 // ----
973 // As an example, the following block contains a normal call from a ----
974 // streaming-compatible function: ----
975 // ----
976 // OrigBB: ----
977 // MSRpstatePseudo 3, 0, %0, 0, <- Conditional SMSTOP ----
978 // bl @normal_callee ----
979 // MSRpstatePseudo 3, 1, %0, 0, <- Conditional SMSTART ----
980 // ----
981 // ...which will be transformed into: ----
982 // ----
983 // OrigBB: ----
984 // TBNZx %0:gpr64, 0, SMBB ----
985 // b EndBB ----
986 // ----
987 // SMBB: ----
988 // MSRpstatesvcrImm1 3, 0, <- SMSTOP ----
989 // ----
990 // EndBB: ----
991 // bl @normal_callee ----
992 // MSRcond_pstatesvcrImm1 3, 1, <- SMSTART ----
993 // ----
994 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
995 ----
996 // Create the conditional branch based on the third operand of the ----
997 // instruction, which tells us if we are wrapping a normal or streaming ----
998 // function. ----
999 // We test the live value of pstate.sm and toggle pstate.sm if this is not the ----
1000 // expected value for the callee (0 for a normal callee and 1 for a streaming ----
1001 // callee). ----
1002 auto PStateSM = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1003 bool IsStreamingCallee = MI.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1004 unsigned Opc = IsStreamingCallee ? AArch64::TBZX : AArch64::TBNZX; 0
1005 MachineInstrBuilder Tbx = ----
1006 BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(Opc)).addReg(PStateSM).addImm(0); 0
1007 ----
1008 // Split MBB and create two new blocks: ----
1009 // - MBB now contains all instructions before MSRcond_pstatesvcrImm1. ----
1010 // - SMBB contains the MSRcond_pstatesvcrImm1 instruction only. ----
1011 // - EndBB contains all instructions after MSRcond_pstatesvcrImm1. ----
1012 MachineInstr &PrevMI = *std::prev(MBBI); 0
1013 MachineBasicBlock *SMBB = MBB.splitAt(PrevMI, /*UpdateLiveIns*/ true); 0
1014 MachineBasicBlock *EndBB = std::next(MI.getIterator()) == SMBB->end() 0
1015 ? *SMBB->successors().begin() 0
1016 : SMBB->splitAt(MI, /*UpdateLiveIns*/ true); 0
1017 ----
1018 // Add the SMBB label to the TB[N]Z instruction & create a branch to EndBB. ----
1019 Tbx.addMBB(SMBB); 0
1020 BuildMI(&MBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::B)) 0
1021 .addMBB(EndBB); 0
1022 MBB.addSuccessor(EndBB); 0
1023 ----
1024 // Create the SMSTART/SMSTOP (MSRpstatesvcrImm1) instruction in SMBB. ----
1025 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*SMBB, SMBB->begin(), MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
1026 TII->get(AArch64::MSRpstatesvcrImm1)); 0
1027 // Copy all but the second and third operands of MSRcond_pstatesvcrImm1 (as ----
1028 // these contain the CopyFromReg for the first argument and the flag to ----
1029 // indicate whether the callee is streaming or normal). ----
1030 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
1031 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
1032 for (unsigned i = 4; i < MI.getNumOperands(); ++i) 0
1033 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(i)); 0
1034 ----
1035 BuildMI(SMBB, DL, TII->get(AArch64::B)).addMBB(EndBB); 0
1036 ----
1037 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1038 return EndBB; 0
1039 } 0
1040 ----
1041 /// If MBBI references a pseudo instruction that should be expanded here, ----
1042 /// do the expansion and return true. Otherwise return false. ----
1043 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandMI(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1044 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI, ----
1045 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &NextMBBI) { ----
1046 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1047 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1048 ----
1049 // Check if we can expand the destructive op ----
1050 int OrigInstr = AArch64::getSVEPseudoMap(MI.getOpcode()); 0
1051 if (OrigInstr != -1) { 0
1052 auto &Orig = TII->get(OrigInstr); 0
1053 if ((Orig.TSFlags & AArch64::DestructiveInstTypeMask) != 0
1054 AArch64::NotDestructive) { ----
1055 return expand_DestructiveOp(MI, MBB, MBBI); 0
1056 } ----
1057 } ----
1058 ----
1059 switch (Opcode) { 0
1060 default: 0
1061 break; 0
1062 ----
1063 case AArch64::BSPv8i8: 0

1297 // We do so by creating a MOVK that sets bits 48-63 of the register to ----
1298 // (global address + 0x100000000 - PC) >> 48. This assumes that we're in ----
1299 // the small code model so we can assume a binary size of <= 4GB, which ----

1498 ----
1499 /// Iterate over the instructions in basic block MBB and expand any ----
1500 /// pseudo instructions. Return true if anything was modified. ----
1501 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::expandMBB(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1502 bool Modified = false; 0
1503 ----
1504 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
1505 while (MBBI != E) { 0
1506 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NMBBI = std::next(MBBI); 0
1507 Modified |= expandMI(MBB, MBBI, NMBBI); 0
1508 MBBI = NMBBI; 0
1509 } ----
1510 ----
1511 return Modified; 0
1512 } ----
1513 ----
1514 bool AArch64ExpandPseudo::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1515 TII = static_cast(MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()); 0
1516 ----
1517 bool Modified = false; 0
1518 for (auto &MBB : MF) 0
1519 Modified |= expandMBB(MBB); 0
1520 return Modified; 0
1521 } ----
1522 ----
1523 /// Returns an instance of the pseudo instruction expansion pass. ----
1524 FunctionPass *llvm::createAArch64ExpandPseudoPass() { 0
1525 return new AArch64ExpandPseudo(); 0
1526 } ----
